Information and cookie settings

When you visit our site, information from your browser may be collected through the use of cookies or similar technologies. We use cookies, among other things, to remember your login information, offer secure login, collect statistics and provide content that is relevant to you. We also use cookies to direct customized marketing to you on our own websites, third party websites and in social channels. If you use a different browser or device, or if you delete cookies from your current browser's cache, we will ask you to update these settings again. More information

Manage Cookie Preferences

Necessary Cookies

Always Active

Our website needs these cookies to work correctly. They enable some basic functionalities, such as online purchases, using logged-in services or chatting with our customer service. These cookies do not store any personal information.

Analysis Cookies

These cookies provide statistics about performance and website visitors. These cookies can be used to count the number of visits and the sources of the website traffic, so that we can measure and improve how the websites work. We can identify which particular pages are most and least popular and can see how visitors navigate around the websites. All the information collected via these cookies is aggregated and anonymous. If you do not give your consent to the use of this type of cookie, we do not see when you visited the websites and will not any receive information about how they are used and work.

Functional Cookies

Always Active

These cookies are used to improve the performance and user experience of the site and to analyze visitors' behavior. They also help us to provide you with a better user experience with more relevant content and enable our website to remember information that changes the way it works or looks. These cookies do not store any personal information.

Marketing and advertising cookies

Marketing and advertising cookies help us analyse and track visitor behaviour so that we can deliver customised content and functions based on user choices and previous visits to the website. Such cookies are also used for so-called re-targeting. This means that we identify you on our website via the cookie and, when you are on another website, are then able to show you marketing from us. For example, we can use Facebook Pixel to show you marketing on Facebook in this way. We can also choose not to show you any marketing and instead direct our marketing towards those who have not yet visited our website. These cookies can also help with customised marketing; e.g. by marketing products/services/functions you have shown an interest in on our website by clicking on information about these products etc. The data collected are your IP address, i.e. a unique ID (combination of numbers and digits) that identifies you when browsing on other websites; this ID is used for the re-targeting explained above
